description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a cheerful and motivated person, who demonstrates a caring, empathetic and compassionate nature, to join our busy Burns team at the Queen Victoria hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will reliable and able to work as a member of the team assisting staff in the daily activities of the ward and providing high standards of care to the patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience in a health care setting is desirable, although full orientation, training and supervison will be provided. Basic IT skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Queen Victoria Hospital offers developmental oppurtunities for Health Care Assistants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be enrolled on the Care certificate and given the oppurtunity to attend training sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lynn Martin&lt;br /&gt;Matron Burns Centre&lt;br /&gt;lynn.martin3@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;01342 414443&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can also Contact Lucy Hall, Deputy Matron 01342 414440&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or Elle Lucas Burns Educator 01342 414440&lt;/p&gt;
